					<div class="cntntTtlUsng" xmlns:msxsl="urn:schemas-microsoft-com:xslt" xmlns:msntvuxp="msntvuxp.microsoft.com">Cut, copy and paste text</div><table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" class="cntntTbl"><tr><td colspan="3" class="shrTxt">Want to copy words from a Web site and then paste them into an e-mail you're writing? Or maybe delete some words from the e-mail you’re about to forward to a friend? You can do both with the Cut, Copy & Paste features.<p> Just select the first word in the text you want to cut or copy, then hold down the <b>Shift</b> key and <b>Right Arrow</b> key until you’ve highlighted the words you want to use. Then:<ul><li>To cut the text, press the <b>CTRL</b> key and the <b>X</b> key at the same time.<li>To copy it, press the <b>CTRL</b> key and the <b>C</b> key at the same time. </ul>Once you've cut or copied some text, you can paste it into a new location. Move your cursor to the spot where you'd like to insert the text, and then press the <b>CTRL</b> key and the <b>V</b> key at the same time.<p> You'll be able to move sentences and paragraphs around your e-mail, or copy sections of Web pages — like a new recipe — without all the retyping.<br></td></tr><tr class="usgBtnRw"><td><input type="button" id="mail12" onClick="javascript:location.href='Tips.aspx'" value="Other Tips" /><img src="/Images/Shared/s.gif" width="15" height="1"><input type="button" id="mail12" onClick="javascript:history.go(-1)" value="Done" /></td></tr></table>
	
